<br>
My point is that we should have a rule saying you can only do vox/naggy once a month.  (each dragon can be hosted by same guild once a month)  This would take into consideration that maybe there are some folks that cannot make it early enough to beat these &quot;top competetors&quot;.  I for one could care less who gets the raids.  I don't care if hunters of the undead get it or if some newby guild gets it.  I just don't like the fact that a guild has the oportunity to take one of these dragons each week cutting others opportunities in half.  Like I said, I myself am not out for these dragons.  Just trying to help others complete the goals they may have set aside.<br>
<br>
Xiaro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=devictionmt>DevictionMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>QHills and Clueless</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#628CBC>(4/26/03 2:13:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=366.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Don't go to Naggy/vox raids</span><hr size=1> A month?  Are you serious?  once a Month?  Get real.  There's epics tied to this.  If you told me I'd only have one shot to getting my epic piece once a month I'd tell you to get bent.  You want to help people complete goals they have?  This is definitely not the way.<br>
<br>
<br>
Ok first of all this really needs to be in another forum.  I understand it pertains to the schedule, but it's really more of a rant about the csm/lada working a lil harder than thou.  Take it to rants or somewhere else.<br>
<br>
Secondly this outpouring of discontent needs to *poof*  HELLO Fimble's already pretty much put the *EOS* stamp on this &quot;problem&quot;.  It's not changing.<br>
<br>
You people are insane.  I've never seen this much bitching before about this.  Hell even lesbian pro-abortion advocates don't spread their message with this much vigor.  <br>
<br>
